<br>
Think about it.  If they made it like Druids highest DS of 24 points.<br>
<br>
Mobs that Quad for whatever damage...  SUPER fast attacks.  That would be 100 mana almost every other second.  Heck, we could barely NUKE that much mana that fast.  So it would either have an insanely short duration, insanely high mana cost (which would defeat the purpose), or an insanely low amount of mana given back.<br>
<br>
Love the idea.  Just would hate to see them rip it to shreads.<br>
<br>
W.F. <p>http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/NEW4.gif</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=marius>Marius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 7:57:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=379.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New spell-line idea</span><hr size=1> Ok, but what if they compare the druid damage shield with the manaabsorptionshield so that they would give about the same indirect damage? <br>
If the druid shield gives for example 15 damage at a given level and we have 1,5 dam/mana with most efficient nuke at that level, make it drain 10 mana a hit. Then it would be as effective damagevise as druidshield (not counting resists.)<br>
<br>
Another idea would be to make it give a percentage of the damage the melee does to the mob.<br>
Call it mana drain or something then. <br>
<br>
